<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="701" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 362.115H21</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Dundee</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DEH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dennison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dundee</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-26"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        July 26, 1915, 11 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>American steamer <hi rend="italic">Leelanaw</hi> of New York, from
                                Archangel to Belfast, with flax, torpedoed and sunk by German
                                submarine on 25th. Whole crew landed at Kirkwall this morning in
                                their own boats. Have instructed consular agent to send them on to
                                Dundee immediately.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DEH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dennison</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>